EncounterFact

The encounter fact contains information about encounters documented in an EMR and encounters derived from billing data. Each row represents an encounter. Encounters from an EMR are flagged with IsDerivedFromBilling = 0 and encounters derived from billing data are flagged with IsDerivedFromBilling = 1. For Epic EMR data, one encounter is one CSN. For encounters derived from billing data, Epic has released definitions that combine multiple outgoing and paid claims into one encounter based on comparing attributes like patient, provider, and date.

    StateOfAuthorization

    : string

    Categorization of the encounter based on when it was authorized. This column returns "Authorized Before Service" if the first time it was authorized was on or before the encounter date. It returns "Authorized After Service" if the first time it was authorized was after the encounter date. It returns "Partially Authorized" if one referral or one coverage was authorized but not all. It returns "Authorization Not Obtained" if none of the referrals or coverages were authorized. It returns "*Not Applicable" if prior authorization was not required.

    Properties

    Data type
    string
    SQL Server data type
    nvarchar(50)
    Allows null
    No
    Default value
    *Unknown
    Delete value
    *Deleted

    If INCL_PRIOR_AUTH_MTRC_YN is "N" then "*Not Applicable" Otherwise if HSP_ACCOUNT.ACCT_FIN_CLASS_C is Medicare then "*Not Applicable" Otherwise if PAT_ENC_HSP.ADT_PAT_CLASS_C is newborn then "*Not Applicable" Otherwise if HSP_ACCOUNT.PRIMARY_PAYOR_ID never needs authorization then "*Not Applicable" Otherwise if PAT_ENC_7.APPT_AUTH_UTC_DDTM <= PAT_ENC_5.APPT_START_UTC_DTTM then "Authorized Before Service" Otherwise if PAT_ENC_7.APPT_AUTH_UTC_DDTM <= PAT_ENC.EFFECTIVE_DATE_DTTM then "Authorized Before Service" Otherwise if PAT_ENC_7.APPT_AUTH_UTC_DDTM is not NULL then "Authorized After Service" Otherwise if PAT_ENC_6.APPT_AUTH_STATUS_C is 3-Partially Authorized then "Partially Authorized" Otherwise if PAT_ENC_7.PRECERT_AUTHORIZATION_STATUS_C = 3-Partially Authorized then "Partially Authorized" Otherwise "Authorization Not Obtained"
